h3. ***Summary*** 
An instance that moved from Server to OnDemand with Mail Archive in the space will cause page move to fail. There is no error thrown in the UI. The error in the logs are as follow
{code}/service/j2ee_confluence/log/main/@40000000546df8a8334cb69c.s:@40000000546df4a2321678bc Caused by: com.atlassian.confluence.pages.DuplicateDataRuntimeException: A page already exists with the title [ Page Title ] in the space with key [ Space Key ]{code}

h3. ***Diagnosing*** 
{code}SELECT title, contentid, contenttype, pluginkey FROM content WHERE spaceid = [ spaceid ] AND title LIKE '%[ Title ]%';{code}

You will notice that there is/are page(s) that is not exact but contains part of the title from the title of the page from the query with the contenttype 'CUSTOM' and pluginkey 'com.atlassian.confluence.plugins.confluence-mail-archiving:mail'

For example a page with the title 'Sample', the query would return

{code:sql}
           title           | contentid | contenttype |                            pluginkey
---------------------------+-----------+-------------+-----------------------------------------------------------------
 Sample - Interest |  16782383 | CUSTOM      | com.atlassian.confluence.plugins.confluence-mail-archiving:mail
{code}

h3. ***Workaround***
Rename Page to be moved. This would still require for support to look into the logs to diagnose the issue.

